# 2. お悩みバレンタイン

Mizuki: Hey, everyone, guess what?!
Mizuki: It's almost...Valentine's Day!
Kanade: Oh, you're right. It's that time of year already...
Ena: Yeah, and the mall's supposed to be having a Valentine's Day fair. I might go check it out to see if they have anything cute.
Mafuyu: So, why is Valentine's Day such a big deal...?
Mizuki: What?! You're kidding, right?! Valentine's Day is a huge event that involves lots of activities! Like giving chocolates to your friends!
Len: Giving chocolates to your friends...?
Ena: Oh, um... Valentine's Day is all about showing appreciation for close acquaintances and the people you care about most.
Mizuki: Which is why you give chocolates to all your friends!
Mizuki: To be fair, it doesn't have to be chocolates. Anything is okay as long as it symbolizes your appreciation for whomever receives your gift♪
Len: I see... That's really nice. You have a whole day dedicated to giving gifts to each other.
Mizuki: Right?! That's why it's such a great event!
Mizuki: So, I say the four of us celebrate Valentine's Day by...giving gifts to Miku and the others!
Ena: Wait, Miku and the others?
Mizuki: Yeah, we should do something for them because they're always there for us!
Ena: Yeah, true...
Kanade: *Nod* I agree...
Mafuyu: ...
Ena: What do you wanna do, Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: I don't know what to give, but I'll try looking for something...
Miku: Thank you. We really appreciate it...
Mizuki: Woohoo! Then, don't forget to bring all your gifts on the day of!
Kanade: (Giving gifts to everyone...)
Kanade: (I want Miku and the others to feel happy... And since we're doing this, I'd like to give something to Mizuki, Ena and Mafuyu...)
Kanade: (But what should I get for them...?)
Len: I'm really looking forward to Valentine's Day now...
Len: But I wish I could do something like Mizuki and the others...
Kanade: Hm...? Len, did you say something?
Len: Huh? Uhh... N-No, it's nothing serious...
Kanade: Oh, okay...
Mizuki: Alright, everyone. Get ready for a really amazing Valentine's Day!
Kanade: Oh, I'm starting to get hungry... I should probably have something to eat...
Kanade: Where did I put the instant noodles...?
Kanade: (Oh, that's right. Ms. Mochizuki's supposed to come over today...)
Kanade: (And she's going to be here soon. In that case, I'll wait until she arrives...)
Kanade: (It's subtle, but Ms. Mochizuki's smile always seems to fade whenever she sees so many instant noodle containers in the garbage...)
Kanade: Oh, I can use this time to look at some of the comments for the video we just uploaded. That shouldn't take up too much of my energy...
Kanade: (Oh, this banner ad... It's for Valentine's Day...)
Kanade: “Chocolates for that special someone”...
Kanade: (Speaking of which, I still haven't decided what I'm going to give everyone...)
Kanade: (And Mizuki's going to bring some homemade sweets. But I can't do anything like that...)
Kanade: What should I do...?
Kanade: Oh, that must be Ms. Mochizuki. I need to go let her in.
Honami: Hello, Ms. Yoisaki. Thank you for having me over again today.
Kanade: Of course. It's always nice having you.
Honami: Have you already had lunch? If not, I can make something while I prepare your other meals.
Kanade: Th-Thank you. I was actually just getting a little hungry...
Honami: Hehe. Okay. Then, I'll get started right way.
Honami: For lunch, I'll be making stewed udon. It's been very cold lately, so I hope it'll help warm you up.
Kanade: Thank you. I'm looking forward to having it.
Kanade: (Ms. Mochizuki's so efficient... Everything seems second nature to her and she doesn't waste any time...)
Kanade: (Not only that, the dishes she makes are all delicious. She really is a talented cook...)
Kanade: (She can even bake her own apple pies. If she can handle something that difficult, then Valentine's Day should be...)
Honami: Um...
Kanade: Huh?
Honami: Can I help you? Is something wrong...?
Kanade: No, um... Sorry, I didn't mean to get in the way.
Honami: No, that's okay.
Honami: It's just... You usually go straight back up to your room, so I began wondering if there was something you wanted to ask me...
Kanade: Oh, um... It's not anything serious...
Kanade: But... If you don't mind listening for a second...
Honami: A gift for Valentine's Day...?
Kanade: Yes, it's something that came up with my group the other day, and I was thinking about what to bring.
Kanade: I briefly considered homemade sweets, but I don't know how to make anything like that.
Kanade: But I owe them all quite a lot, so I'd like to take this opportunity to properly thank them somehow.
Honami: I see. And that's why you seemed preoccupied...
Honami: Hehe. I didn't realize that you were also in the same predicament...
Kanade: Huh? Also...?
Honami: Oh, I'm sorry. The truth is, Ichika asked me for some advice regarding this very subject just the other day.
Kanade: Hoshino did...? Is she also planning on making something?
Honami: Yes, she'd already whittled her options down to jewelry or other accessories, but I gave her a few other ideas to go along with that.
Kanade: Accessories? I see. Yes, that is an option...
Honami: It is. However, I believe a Valentine's Day gift can take any shape as long as it symbolizes your appreciation for the person receiving it.
Kanade: I agree with you there. So, what did you suggest that she make?
Honami: I gave her a few suggestions, but she ended up going with scented candles.
Kanade: Scented candles...? You can make those yourself? I'm not sure I could...
Honami: That's not true. Anyone can make them as long as they have all the necessary ingredients.
Honami: Oh, actually. Ms. Yoisaki, if you'd like...
